OL,3,CReform UK threatens to scrap #30m of
OL,4,CBangor University funding if elected
OL,6,FThe society - which operates
OL,7,Findependently through the Students'
OL,8,FUnion rather than being controlled by
OL,9,FBangor University - stated they
OL,10,Fmaintain "zero tolerance for any form
OL,11,Fof racism, transphobia, or homophobia
OL,12,Fdisplayed by the members of Reform UK".
OL,14,FResponding to the society's decision,
OL,15,Fin a social media post Reform UK's
OL,16,Fhead of policy, said if elected a
OL,17,FReform UK government would slash #30m
OL,18,Fin funding to the Welsh institution,
OL,19,Fdespite the debate refusal originating
OL,20,Ffrom the student society rather than
OL,21,Fthe university administration.
